        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 30 at 4:55PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 454 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Monroe, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Monroe, Luna Pier, La Salle, Estral Beach, Toledo Beach, Woodland
Beach, Stony Point, Bolles Harbor, and Detroit Beach.

People attending Monroe County Fair  should seek safe shelter
immediately!
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
